DataElement.preferredName: Dose Time Elapsed Derived Minute Number
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Derived numeric value to represent the number of minutes that have elapsed from the start time of an infusion or agent administration until the time of the collection of a biological sample.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Chronological relationship between a dosing event and an observation made and other relevant associated periods of time.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: The amount of medicine taken, or radiation given, at one time.

Concepts.definition: A quantity of an agent (such as substance or energy) administered, taken, or absorbed at one time.

Property.preferredDefinition: The chronological relationship between when an observation is made and other relevant associated periods of time.  For example, the timing axis specifies whether a given observation represents the value of a measurement at a moment (point) in time, an average of the measurement over a period of time (24 hours, 72 hours, a nursing shift, a clinical encounter), a minimum or maximum over a period of time (24 hour maximum), or its ordinal rank within a period of time (first, second, last).

Concepts.definition: The chronological relationship between when an observation is made and other relevant associated periods of time.  For example, the timing axis specifies whether a given observation represents the value of a measurement at a moment (point) in time, an average of the measurement over a period of time (24 hours, 72 hours, a nursing shift, a clinical encounter), a minimum or maximum over a period of time (24 hour maximum), or its ordinal rank within a period of time (first, second, last).

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: actions or administration of therapeutic agents to produce an effect that is intended to alter the course of a pathologic process (NCI).

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the number of minutes that have elapsed between two events.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: Number; a concept of quantity derived from zero and units; a numeral or string of numerals that is used for identification.

Concepts.definition: A numeral or string of numerals expressing value, quantity, or identification.
